## 5. Post-Processing: [weldMesh.ts](file:///c:/Users/patij212/Downloads/PotFoundry-Lite-v2.0/potfoundry-web/src/utils/geometry/weldMesh.ts) & [stitchSeam](file:///c:/Users/patij212/Downloads/PotFoundry-Lite-v2.0/potfoundry-web/src/utils/geometry/ConstrainedTriangulator.ts#791-881)

**Role**: CPU welding. Merges duplicate vertices to form a watertight manifold.

**Function**: [stitchSeam](file:///c:/Users/patij212/Downloads/PotFoundry-Lite-v2.0/potfoundry-web/src/utils/geometry/ConstrainedTriangulator.ts#791-881) (in [ConstrainedTriangulator.ts](file:///c:/Users/patij212/Downloads/PotFoundry-Lite-v2.0/potfoundry-web/src/utils/geometry/ConstrainedTriangulator.ts))
| Line Range | Logic | Status | Critical Analysis |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **831-844** | **Topology Welding** | **PARTIAL** | Identifies vertices at $x \approx 1$ and remaps them to $x \approx 0$. <br> **Reality**: It successfully welds the *boundary* vertices (added at 0.0/1.0). It validates the mesh is "closed". But it does NOT fix the feature gap because the feature vertices are at 0.005/0.995 and are technically "interior" vertices, not boundary vertices. |

**File**: [weldMesh.ts](file:///c:/Users/patij212/Downloads/PotFoundry-Lite-v2.0/potfoundry-web/src/utils/geometry/weldMesh.ts)
| Line Range | Logic | Status | Critical Analysis |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **25-30** | **Key Generation** | **CRITICAL FAIL** | `const key = \`\${x}_\${y}_\${z}\``. Creates millions of short-lived strings. V8 Garbage Collector chokes on this, causing the "Physical Limit" crash. |
| **38-46** | **Hash Map** | **FAIL** | Using a `Map<string, number>` is memory inefficient. For 4M triangles (2M verts), this consumes 100s of MBs of heap just for string pointers. |

